  "prompt": "What has replaced CGI (common gateway interface) in today's web?",
  "response": "Modern web development has largely replaced CGI with more advanced technologies and frameworks, including:\n\n1. Web Application Frameworks\n- Django (Python)\n- Ruby on Rails\n- Express.js (Node.js)\n- ASP.NET\n- Laravel (PHP)\n\n2. RESTful APIs\n- Built using various languages and technologies\n- Typically use JSON for data exchange\n- More lightweight and efficient than CGI\n\n3. Serverless Computing\n- AWS Lambda\n- Google Cloud Functions\n- Azure Functions\n\n4. Backend Technologies\n- FastAPI\n- Spring Boot\n- Node.js with Express\n- Go web frameworks\n\n5. WebSockets\n- Real-time, two-way communication\n- Enables more dynamic web applications\n\n6. GraphQL\n- Flexible query language for APIs\n- Allows clients to request specific data\n\nThese technologies offer improved performance, better scalability, easier development, and more robust security compared to traditional CGI scripts. They provide more efficient ways of handling web requests, generating dynamic content, and managing server-side logic.\n\nModern web applications typically use a combination of these technologies to create responsive, interactive web experiences.",
